Author: Mark81#4505
Content: Those supernet assetchains that were migrated to komodo ecosystem are there for a reason and that is revenue flow for original supernet investors that invested to james vision. Once things are set in place various services that are build on komodo ecosystem will bring revenue flow for those asset addresses that hold coins like dex, supernet, revs to same address on kmd chain.

Author: Mark81#4505
Content: Assetchain holdings present revenue share size of total amount to be paid in each address that hold coins. If i remember correctly assetchains have 1 million coins and payout is always done when it reaches 1 million dollars in usd. So one asset coin gets you one dollar worth of KMD.

I skimmed the Komodo whitepaper and it doesn't really mention payouts of superNET assetchains.

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: SuperNET assetchains are INDEPENDENT of KMD

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: they are built on top of KMD, but not in KMD itself

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: in some jurisdictions, having revshare makes it regulated and I didnt want to entangle KMD in such things. (yes, I foresaw this years before it became an issue)

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: if KMD is the infrastructure (roads, electricity, water, ...) think of the SuperNET assetchains as the buildings that are built on top of it

SuperNET had great ideas but they didn't really have the infrastructure necessary, so KMD was born out of necessity to be a fuel for all these ideas, in a sense?
